choices.text:
worrying about my spending money, making sure I keep up with my schoolwork and being involved with my community. I also help as an interpreter because my dad doesn’t speak much English. This makes my mom my biggest influence.

I’ve been to New Zealand, Czech Republic and Jamaica. I love watching anime, I occasionally draw and I do practice the flute extensively.

If you had one thing to do before you die, what would it be? One thing I would like to do is skydive. I would like to swim with the dolphins and cage dive with sharks (I’m one of those weird people that actually likes sharks). Debuting in hearing world was also one experience I really enjoyed.
